  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Orthopedic implant wear credibility assessment (NC-4 negative control)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for finite-element wear prediction of a total knee replacement (TKR) tibial insert under standard gait loading. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can predict relative polyethylene wear volume for a Class II orthopedic implant at Model Risk Level 3. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors are fully assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at MRL 3. Monte Carlo sensitivity analysis on material property inputs and boundary-condition magnitude is documented. Decision: Accepted. This package is a clean NC-4 negative-control archetype; no weakener should fire.",
