      "description": "FE-predicted peak contact pressure at 30° flexion compared against Fujifilm Prescale measurements from five cadaveric specimens. Mean predicted: 18.4 MPa; mean measured: 17.9 MPa; relative error 2.8%. Sensitivity analysis confirmed contact pressure predictions are most sensitive to UHMWPE elastic modulus (±12% response to ±10% input variation) and least sensitive to femoral geometry tolerances (±1.5% response)."
    }
