        "description": "Quantitative metric: NRMSE ≤ 0.10 between predicted and measured cumulative wear volume at 5 Mc. Qualitative metric: predicted wear scar location and morphology visually consistent with post-test surface profilometry maps (medial plateau dominant wear pattern). Both criteria must be satisfied. Achieved Level 3 reflects quantitative NRMSE = 0.061 and documented qualitative pattern comparison."
      },
      "rationale": "NRMSE = 0.061 across three simulator runs, well within acceptance threshold. Wear scar morphology (medial-dominant, anterior-shifted) matches profilometry maps from all three physical specimens. Comparison documented in validation report VR-2024-01."
