        "description": "Primary QoI (cumulative wear volume at 5 Mc) is the direct input to the design ranking decision. Secondary QoI (peak contact pressure) is a mechanistic intermediate that drives wear model predictions. Both QoIs are clinically relevant (wear debris generation linked to osteolysis risk). Achieved Level 2 reflects documented traceability from QoI to COU decision criterion."
      },
      "rationale": "Wear volume is the primary design selection criterion per the regulatory submission plan. Peak contact pressure is the dominant driver of the Archard wear model and was confirmed as the most influential input in the sensitivity analysis. Traceability matrix linking QoIs to COU decision documented in credibility plan CP-2024-01."
