        "description": "Validation experiments use the same ISO 14243-1 gait waveform, same UHMWPE grade (GUR 1050), same femoral component material (CoCr), and same tibial insert geometry family as the COU device. Lubricant and temperature match COU physiological conditions. Achieved Level 2 reflects high fidelity between validation scenario and COU without requiring in vivo retrieval data."
      },
      "rationale": "The validation wear simulator test uses identical loading waveforms, same material grade, and same geometric family as the candidate designs being evaluated. The only departure from COU is the use of bovine serum surrogate for synovial fluid, which is standard per ISO 14243-1 and accepted by regulatory guidance."
    },
