        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form: Archard wear law with cross-shear correction documented and justified",
        "description": "Archard wear law with cross-shear correction (Turell et al. 2004) selected based on published benchmarks for UHMWPE wear under multidirectional sliding. Model form selection documented with comparison to alternative wear laws (Archard without cross-shear, energy-based wear model). Archard with cross-shear demonstrated lowest NRMSE in published literature for equivalent loading conditions. Achieved Level 2 reflects documented model form selection rationale."
      },
      "rationale": "Archard wear law with cross-shear correction is the most widely validated wear model for UHMWPE under multidirectional gait loading per published literature (Turell 2004, Goreham-Voss 2010, Willing 2011). Model form selection documented in credibility plan section 4.2. Alternative energy-based model considered but rejected due to higher parameter uncertainty at MRL 3."
    },
    {
