        "description": "ISO 14243-1 loading waveforms as applied in FE model compared point-by-point against digitized simulator control waveforms. Maximum deviation between FE input and simulator waveform: < 2% of peak value for all five DOFs. Lubricant viscosity effect on contact modeled via effective friction coefficient calibrated from simulator friction torque measurements. Achieved Level 2 reflects documented waveform equivalency check."
      },
      "rationale": "Waveform equivalency check performed by digitizing simulator control signals at 100 Hz and comparing to FE boundary condition time histories. Maximum deviation: 1.4% (AP displacement waveform, mid-stance). Friction coefficient µ = 0.04 calibrated from simulator torque measurements, consistent with published bovine serum lubrication data for CoCr-UHMWPE."
